<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Theme Select</h1>\n\n<p>A theme select is a headless component that allows users to switch between different visual themes or color schemes using a native <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> dropdown. It is commonly used to offer light, dark, high-contrast, or other visual modes, enhancing personalization and accessibility by letting users adapt the interface to their preferences or environment.</p>\n\n<p>The consumer provides <code>&lt;option&gt;</code> elements as children to define the available themes. The component uses <code>aria-label</code> for accessible naming and supports two-way binding on the selected theme.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders a <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> element with class <code>theme-select</code></li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the root element for consumer customization</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Help</h2>\n\n<p>Use ThemeSelect when you need a dropdown for switching visual themes. Common scenarios include light/dark mode toggles, high-contrast themes for accessibility, or branded theme options. Pair with ThemeSelectOption for individual options, or use plain <code>&lt;option&gt;</code> elements.</p>\n\n<h2>Syntax</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;ThemeSelect label=\"...\" value={value}&gt;\n  &lt;option value=\"...\"&gt;...&lt;/option&gt;\n&lt;/ThemeSelect&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<p>Basic light/dark theme dropdown:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;ThemeSelect label=\"Theme\" value={theme}&gt;\n  &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"light\"&gt;Light&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n  &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"dark\"&gt;Dark&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n&lt;/ThemeSelect&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<p>Extended theme options with system default:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;ThemeSelect label=\"Color scheme\" value={theme}&gt;\n  &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"system\"&gt;System Default&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n  &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"light\"&gt;Light&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n  &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"dark\"&gt;Dark&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n  &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"high-contrast\"&gt;High Contrast&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n&lt;/ThemeSelect&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<p>In a settings form:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;Form label=\"Preferences\" onSubmit={handleSubmit}&gt;\n  &lt;Field label=\"Theme\"&gt;\n    &lt;ThemeSelect label=\"Theme\" value={theme}&gt;\n      &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"\" disabled&gt;Choose a theme...&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n      &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"light\"&gt;Light&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n      &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"dark\"&gt;Dark&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n      &lt;ThemeSelectOption value=\"high-contrast\"&gt;High Contrast&lt;/ThemeSelectOption&gt;\n    &lt;/ThemeSelect&gt;\n  &lt;/Field&gt;\n  &lt;Button type=\"submit\"&gt;Save&lt;/Button&gt;\n&lt;/Form&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr><th>Prop</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>label</code></td><td><code>string</code></td><td>(required)</td><td>Accessible name applied via <code>aria-label</code></td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>value</code></td><td><code>string</code></td><td><code>\"\"</code></td><td>Bindable string representing the currently selected theme</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>children</code></td><td><code>slot</code></td><td>(required)</td><td><code>&lt;option&gt;</code> elements representing available themes</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>...restProps</code></td><td>HTML attributes</td><td></td><td>Additional attributes spread onto the <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> element</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Examples</h2>\n\n<p>With theme application:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;ThemeSelect label=\"Choose theme\" value={theme}&gt;\n  &lt;option value=\"light\"&gt;Light&lt;/option&gt;\n  &lt;option value=\"dark\"&gt;Dark&lt;/option&gt;\n&lt;/ThemeSelect&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Tab: Moves focus to and from the select element (native browser behavior)</li>\n<li>Space/Enter: Opens the dropdown list when focused (native browser behavior)</li>\n<li>Arrow Up/Down: Navigates through theme options (native browser behavior)</li>\n<li>Escape: Closes the dropdown list (native browser behavior)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>aria-label={label}</code> -- provides an accessible name for the theme select since there is no visible <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> element</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use for selecting a visual theme from a dropdown when space is limited.</li>\n<li>Use as a compact alternative to ThemePicker when there are many theme options.</li>\n<li>Use in navigation bars, toolbars, or sidebars where a dropdown fits the layout better than radio buttons.</li>\n<li>Use when theme options do not need visual previews or swatches.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use when visual preview of themes is important -- use <a href=\"../theme-picker/\">ThemePicker</a> with swatches instead.</li>\n<li>Do not use for non-theme selections -- use <a href=\"../select/\">Select</a> with custom options instead.</li>\n<li>Do not use for a simple binary light/dark toggle -- use <a href=\"../switch-button/\">SwitchButton</a> or <a href=\"../toggle-button/\">ToggleButton</a> instead.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This headless component provides a native <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> element with an <code>aria-label</code> for accessible theme switching. Keyboard navigation and dropdown behavior come from the browser's native select. The consumer provides <code>&lt;option&gt;</code> children (or ThemeSelectOption components) and all visual styling.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.theme-select</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> element with class <code>theme-select</code></li>\n<li>Verify aria-label={label}<code> -- provides an accessible name for the theme select since there is no visible </code>&lt;label&gt;` element</li>\n<li>Verify keyboard interactions work correctly</li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Ensure the selected option clearly indicates the active theme. Consider showing a preview swatch next to each option label.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Apply the selected theme value to the document root (e.g., <code>data-theme</code> attribute or CSS class) and persist the choice across sessions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>ThemeSelect contains ThemeSelectOption children (or plain <code>&lt;option&gt;</code> elements) following the Select/SelectOption pattern. ThemeSelect is also related to ThemePicker (radio-based approach) and ThemeView (read-only display).</p>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>theme-select-option</code> — one option in a theme select dropdown</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>MDN select element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select</li>\n<li>WCAG 1.4.12 Text Spacing (theme customization): https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/text-spacing.html</li>\n</ul>";
  // BEGIN auto-generated component example consts
  const demoHtml: string = "<select class=\"theme-select\" aria-label=\"Choose theme\"><option class=\"theme-select-option\" value=\"light\">Light</option><option class=\"theme-select-option\" value=\"dark\">Dark</option></select>";
  const svelteSource: string = "// In your Svelte component:\nimport ThemeSelect from \"lily-design-system-svelte-headless/components/ThemeSelect/ThemeSelect.svelte\";\n\n<ThemeSelect>\n  <!-- content -->\n</ThemeSelect>\n";
  // END auto-generated component example consts
</script>

